<br>
-Kael: Go to Arena and farm armor. Not only will you be increasing your crew's gear, but you'll also be getting exp, which is your group's biggest disadvantage, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
-Ssra: Go farm Rings of the Shissar parts. Again, not only will you be increasing your crew's gear, but you'll also be getting exp. Also keep an eye out for Rhag 1, you might be able to put a decent sized dent in him, or atleast you'll know what you need to work on in the future.<br>
<br>
-Sebilis: Sebilite Protector in Trak's Lair. This might not be nearly as good as it once was in terms of a good training mob, but when a lot of guilds first entered Kunark, here was one mob to refine your tactics and still get a bit of a challenge. Farm Juggs while you are down there maybe, good exp and you'll get some needed spell drops.<br>
<br>
-Akheva: You might want to try Va Dyn, just to see how you do. Since you didn't post a class make up or anything I'm really unsure exactly what you might or might not be capable of. As soon as you have a beefy tank, and a Cleric to keep him alive, this is a good mob to try.<br>
<br>
-Velketors: Lord Dojo. Pretty easy practice mob, the basics you learn on this mob will be the basis for many of your future fights. Decent loot upgrades for Monks, and maybe a few other classes..?<br>
<br>
